criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age of 18 - 60 years;

          2. American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) physical status of I - II;

          3. Patients scheduled for urinary, obstetrics and gynecology surgery in supine position
             or lithotomy position under general anesthesia, and the expected operation time is
             more than 1 hour;

          4. Patients and their authorized surrogates have signed the informed consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients who have difficulty in applying pulmonary ultrasound, such as chest
             fractures, surgical history, etc;

          2. Patients who have a history of upper respiratory tract infection one month before
             surgery, or a history of smoking more than 6 packs/year;

          3. Preoperative chest X-ray or CT abnormalities, including atelectasis, pneumothorax,
             pleural effusion or pneumonia;

          4. BMI>30kg/㎡;

          5. Expected difficulty in intubation or mask ventilation;

          6. Patients with significant increase in intraocular pressure and intracranial pressure
             before surgery;

          7. Patients allergic to S-ketamine, propofol and opioids.

          8. Patients with a positive history of psychiatric disorders.
